          <tr>
            <td width="100%" valign="top" align="left" colspan="2">
              </td>
          </tr>

<tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left" colspan="2"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0">&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left" colspan="2"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0"><img border="0" src="../triangle.JPG"><font size="3" face="Tahoma" color="#004242"><b>SOLOING WITH YOUR WIZARD</b></font></td></tr><tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left" colspan="2"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0">&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td width="20%" valign="top" align="left"><b><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Group / Solo:</font></b></td><td width="80%" valign="top" align="left"><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Solo - Wizard</font></td></tr><tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left" colspan="2"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0">&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td width="20%" valign="top" align="left"><b><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Mob Level:</font></b></td><td width="80%" valign="top" align="left"><font size="2" face="Tahoma">1 to 40</font></td></tr><tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left" colspan="2"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0">&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td width="20%" valign="top" align="left"><b><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Zone:</font></b></td><td width="80%" valign="top" align="left"><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Erudin, Palace</font></td></tr><tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left" colspan="2"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0">&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td width="20%" valign="top" align="left"><b><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Location:</font></b></td><td width="80%" valign="top" align="left"><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Several different zones</font></td></tr><tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left" colspan="2"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0">&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td width="20%" valign="top" align="left"><b><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Character Level:</font></b></td><td width="80%" valign="top" align="left"><font size="2" face="Tahoma">1 to 50</font></td></tr><tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left" colspan="2"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0">&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td width="20%" valign="top" align="left"><b><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Strategy:</font></b></td><td width="80%" valign="top" align="left"><font size="2" face="Tahoma">The best way to play your wizard.
<br><br>
This guide will help you get your wizard to 50+ in a very short time. I was able to get my wizard to 50 in less then 23 days played.
<br><br>
First off, if you plan on being a wizard you need to be Erudiate. Highest INT allows you to max out with +mana items very easily. Dump as many points as you can into INT, put any extra points into STR, this comes in handy if you don’t have tinker bags and you are carrying around a lot of loot.
<br><br>
Don’t waste any time in Tox Forest or Erudin. Get a port to West Commons as soon as possible, run to North Freeport, and get binded. Go on a rat/bat killing spree till level 5. Always have your Damage Shield on and you should do fine. Also a little trick for those with fast connections and little patience is to do this. If you are out of mana and don’t feel like medding. Just attack the guards, you will die and come back right where you bound, with full mana. This trick only works from level 1 to 5, before you start losing exp for dying. This method is not recommended but can be done.
<br><br>
After you hit level 5 move to East Commons and begin hunting near the tunnel. You should be able to pull rogue asps and other mobs to the tunnel. If you get in any trouble there should be plenty of people to help you out, or you can just zone. Stay here until level 8.
<br><br>
From level 8 to 11 spend your time in North Ro, keeping the platform as your camp. Bind here as soon as you are able to. Begin pulling rogue mobs to the platform, using a basic root/nuke strategy. If you are finding this too hard, get a group hunting dervs. 
<br><br>
At level 11 you should move to Oasis. Use the docks as your camp. You can easily make it to 18 here killing anything that cons blue. Orc alley is a great place for a wizard to solo if you can pull right. Grouping here is not recommended.
<br><br>
From level 18 to 21 go to Lake Rather and kill aviaks. The best camp is at the zone to the Arena. There are 2 guards that spawn with 4 minutes between each. With good timing you should be able to kill both nonstop. If you get in any trouble zone into the Arena.
<br><br>
At level 21 move to South Karana. Move to the Aviak tree and bind there. You can start by soloing darters, then slowly up to rooks and then avocets. Most people leave here around 26, but you can easily level up on Avocets to 29. If you get into any trouble you can zone into Lake Rather. As soon as you hit 29 you get the most important wizard spell. Bonds of Force. This spell allows you to snare your target and any other targets close to it. 
<br><br>
When you hit 29 you should immediately move to South Ro, and begin the long camp for J boots. These boots will allow you to outrun your target while it is snared, stopping for a moment, nuking, and then running again. This method is known as “Kiting” To get J boots first you need to get the Ring of the Ancients from the Ancient Cyclops in South Ro. There is almost always a group camping him so try and join up with them, the Cyclops might be too much of a match for you to solo him. Once you get the ring, you need to obtain a shadowed rapier, which can be found off shadowed men, in many zones. Bring the ring Shadowed rapier, and 3250 gold to Hasten Bootstrudder found in Rather Mountains. Then you will get the boots.
<br><br>
When you have Jboots, move to West Karana. Find the barbarian fishing camp along the water and begin hunting a fisherman “Ulrich”. This will ruin your Hallas faction, but it is well worth it. If Ulrich is taken you can alternate hunting the corrupt guards near the barbarian camp. You can then take the bracers they drop and give them to the captain on the bridge in North Karana. (Just gate there) You will get exp, money, and bronze. After you have gained a few levels you can start killing Einhorst as well. He is Ulrich’s slightly higher-level brother. If you get into any trouble you can zone into Qeynos Hills. Stay here until you are level 40.
<br><br>
At level 40 its time to make a trip back to Oasis. Spec Island is your new home. Learn the art of single pulling specs and kiting them. You will have non-stop exp. You can experiment kiting more then 1 spec at a time using AE spells; Circle of Force is by far the most mana efficient spell to use in this way. If you get into any trouble you can zone into NRO or SRO. Stay here killing specs until level 46.
<br><br>
At 46 move to Dreadlands and bind right outside Karnors Castle. Pick up loose mobs off the sides of the Castle and kite them. You can easily get to 50 this way. If you get stuck in a bad situation you can zone in Karnors Castle.
<br><br>
This is a very boring, very monotonous way to level up, but it will work very quickly.</font></td></tr><tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left" colspan="2"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0">&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td width="20%" valign="top" align="left"><b><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Author:</font></b></td><td width="80%" valign="top" align="left"><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Diables (Rodcet Nife)</font></td></tr><tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left" colspan="2"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0">&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td width="20%" valign="top" align="left"><b><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Rating:</font></b></td><td width="80%" valign="top" align="left"><font size="2" face="Tahoma"><b>6.5</b> (average of <b>24</b> votes)</font></td></tr><tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left" colspan="2"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0">&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td width="20%" valign="top" align="left" valign="middle"><b><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Rate this spot:</font></b></td><td width="80%" valign="top" align="left" valign="middle"><font size="2" face="Tahoma"><FORM ACTION = "ratehg.asp" METHOD = post><SELECT NAME="Voting"><OPTION VALUE="0">Rate this Spot</OPTION><OPTION VALUE="1">1 - Don't even bother</OPTION><OPTION VALUE="2">2</OPTION><OPTION VALUE="3">3</OPTION><OPTION VALUE="4">4</OPTION><OPTION VALUE="5">5 - It is ok</OPTION><OPTION VALUE="6">6</OPTION><OPTION VALUE="7">7</OPTION><OPTION VALUE="8">8</OPTION><OPTION VALUE="9">9</OPTION><OPTION VALUE="10">10 - You must come here</OPTION></SELECT><INPUT TYPE = "hidden" NAME = "intHGID" VALUE = 126><INPUT TYPE = "submit" VALUE="Rate It!"></form></font></td></tr><tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left" colspan="2"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0">&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left" colspan="2"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-h